SCRAP
  Destroy a ship, plane, or land unit and recover some of its build
  materials into the sector it's standing in.

SYNTAX
  scrap s <ship-spec>
  scrap p <plane-spec>
  scrap l <land-spec>

DESCRIPTION
  Recovers 2/3 of the unit's LCM/HCM build cost, scaled by its current
  efficiency, dumped into the sector it's in. Any cargo the unit is
  carrying (ships, land units) spills into the sector too.

  <ship-spec>/<plane-spec>/<land-spec> - uid, uid range, comma list,
                 "*" for all owned, "~" for units with no fleet/wing/
                 army assigned, or a fleet/wing/army letter (see
                 'info fleetadd'/'info wingadd'/'info army').

  Requirements depend on type:
    ships       - must be in a friendly harbor at >=60% efficiency
    planes      - must be in a friendly airfield at >=60% efficiency
    land units  - must be in a friendly (same-owner) sector

  Ships: scrapping drops efficiency below 20% (SHIP_MINEFF), which
  sinks it -- ownership is cleared immediately, so it disappears from
  your fleet for good and can't be rebuilt or re-scrapped. Planes and
  land units don't have this rule (matches 4.4.1): they persist at 0%
  efficiency and *will* rebuild from scratch if their sector still has
  LCM/HCM flowing to it, exactly like a freshly laid keel. If you
  don't want a scrapped plane/land unit coming back, scrap it
  somewhere without spare LCM/HCM, or stop distributing those in.

  Use 'scuttle' instead if you don't care about recovering materials
  and just want it gone regardless of where it is.

EXAMPLE
  scrap s 12                scrap ship 12 in its harbor
  scrap p 5-8                scrap planes 5 through 8
  scrap l a                 scrap every land unit in army 'a'

SEE ALSO
  scuttle  build  ship  plane  land  fleetadd  wingadd  army
